# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT MODE — uncomment exactly one block
# =============================================================================
#
# IMPORTANT: The mode must match how you are running the services.
#
#   CONTAINER MODE  → use when running with `docker compose up`
#                     All inter-service calls use Docker internal DNS.
#                     Do NOT use localhost values with Docker Compose — inside
#                     a container, localhost resolves to that container itself,
#                     not the host machine, so cross-service calls will fail.
#
#   LOCAL MODE      → use when running each service directly with `go run`
#                     (no Docker). All services share the host network so
#                     localhost works for everything, including JWKS fetch.
#                     Do NOT use local mode values inside Docker Compose.
#
# =============================================================================

# -- CONTAINER MODE (active) --------------------------------------------------
AUTH_SERVER_ORIGIN=http://auth-server:8081
RESOURCE_SERVER_ORIGIN=http://resource-server:8082
REQUESTING_APP_ORIGIN=http://requesting-app:3000

# -- LOCAL MODE (go run, no Docker) -------------------------------------------
# AUTH_SERVER_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8081
# RESOURCE_SERVER_ORIGIN=http://localhost:8082
# REQUESTING_APP_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000
